Ex. No: 7 — Create and Index a Pandas Series and DataFrame

From the uploaded FDS manual

Aim

To create and index Pandas Series and DataFrame objects.

Theory

Pandas Series is a one-dimensional data structure.
DataFrame is a two-dimensional table with rows and columns.
Indexing helps access specific data easily.

Software / Tools Required
•
Python 3.x
•
Anaconda Distribution
•
Jupyter Notebook / Google Colab / IDLE
•
Pandas Library

Program
import pandas as pd

# Creating Series
marks = pd.Series([78, 85, 62, 90],
                  index=['Maths', 'Physics', 'Chemistry', 'AI'])

print("Pandas Series:")
print(marks)

# Accessing values
print("\nMarks in Physics:", marks['Physics'])
print("Marks using position index:", marks.iloc[2])

# Creating DataFrame
data = {
    'Name': ['Ravi', 'Anu', 'Kumar', 'Divya'],
    'Department': ['AI&DS', 'CSE', 'AI&DS', 'ECE'],
    'Marks': [88, 92, 79, 85]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

print("\nPandas DataFrame:")
print(df)

# loc indexing
print("\nUsing loc:")
print(df.loc[1])

# iloc indexing
print("\nUsing iloc:")
print(df.iloc[2])

# Selecting column
print("\nMarks Column:")
print(df['Marks'])


Procedure
Open Jupyter Notebook.
Import Pandas library.
Create a Pandas Series.
Assign custom indexes.
Access Series elements.
Create DataFrame using dictionary.
Display DataFrame.
Use loc for label indexing.
Use iloc for position indexing.
Execute and verify output.


